    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The culture, style, and period in the development of a peoples when they begin using very small stone tools, often combined with wood, bone, resin and fiber to form a composite tool or weapon, such as the points of spears and arrows. Microlithic culture developed at different times in different places throughout the world.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000007241/Cambridge Encyclopedia of Archaeology (1980)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De cultuur, stijl en periode in de ontwikkeling van een volk wanneer dit heel kleine stenen gereedschappen gaat gebruiken, vaak in combinatie met hout, been, hars en vezels, om een samengesteld gereedschap of wapen te maken, zoals speren en pijlen met punten. Microlithische culturen ontwikkelden zich in verschillende perioden op verschillende plekken over de hele wereld.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
